{"abstract":[{"text":"Organize dependency injection across multiple Swift Package Manager modules.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/forge\/modulararchitecture"]}],"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/ModularArchitecture","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"metadata":{"title":"Modular Architecture","roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"Forge"}]},"seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Architecture-and-Best-Practices","title":"Architecture and Best Practices","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/SOLIDPrinciples","doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/XcodePreviewSupport"],"generated":true}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In a modular codebase, each SPM module owns its own ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/Container","type":"reference"},{"text":" subclass. This","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"keeps dependency boundaries clean, makes modules independently testable, and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"prevents accidental cross-module coupling.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"One Container per Module","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"One-Container-per-Module"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Each module defines exactly one container that manages all dependencies for that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"module. The container file includes the module-local typealias:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["\/\/ FeatureAuth\/Sources\/AuthContainer.swift","","import Forge","import CoreProtocols","","typealias Inject<T> = ContainerInject<AuthContainer, T>","","public final class AuthContainer: Container, SharedContainer {","    public static var shared = AuthContainer()","","    public var authService: any AuthServiceProtocol {","        provide(.singleton, preview: { MockAuthService() }) {","            AuthService(network: self.networkClient)","        }","    }","","    public var networkClient: any NetworkClientProtocol {","        provide(.singleton) { URLSessionNetworkClient() }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"All ","type":"text"},{"code":"@Inject","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" usages within the module use the bare syntax — no container name visible:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["\/\/ FeatureAuth\/Sources\/LoginViewModel.swift","","final class LoginViewModel: ObservableObject {","    @Inject(\\.authService) private var auth","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Cross-Module Proxying","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Cross-Module-Proxying"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Feature modules must not import other feature modules directly. If a module needs a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"dependency owned by another module, it "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"proxies"}]},{"type":"text","text":" the dependency through its own"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"container:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ FeatureSearch\/Sources\/SearchContainer.swift","","import Forge","import CoreAnalytics","","public final class SearchContainer: Container, SharedContainer {","    public static var shared = SearchContainer()","","    \/\/ Proxy — delegates to another module's container","    public var analytics: any AnalyticsProtocol {","        provide { CoreAnalyticsContainer.shared.analytics }","    }","","    public var searchService: any SearchServiceProtocol {","        provide(.singleton) {","            SearchService(analytics: self.analytics)","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Benefits-of-Proxying","text":"Benefits of Proxying","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Test isolation"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — override "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"analytics"},{"type":"text","text":" on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SearchContainer"},{"type":"text","text":" directly, without"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"touching "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CoreAnalyticsContainer"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Clean dependency graph","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — each module’s DI surface is fully within its own container","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Swappability"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — if "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CoreAnalytics"},{"type":"text","text":" is replaced, only the proxy property needs updating"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"The-Composition-Root","text":"The Composition Root","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The app target is the "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"composition root"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — the only place where all modules are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"imported and containers are wired together:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["\/\/ App\/Sources\/AppDelegate.swift","","import FeatureAuth","import FeatureSearch","import CoreAnalytics","","class AppDelegate: UIApplicationDelegate {","    func application(","        _ application: UIApplication,","        didFinishLaunchingWithOptions launchOptions: [UIApplication.LaunchOptionsKey: Any]?","    ) -> Bool {","        \/\/ Wire containers","        AuthContainer.shared = AuthContainer()","        SearchContainer.shared = SearchContainer()","        CoreAnalyticsContainer.shared = CoreAnalyticsContainer()","        return true","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Import-Dependency-Graph","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Import Dependency Graph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The correct architecture follows this pattern:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["CoreProtocols (protocols only — no Forge import)","       ^","       |","  Feature modules (each has its own Container)","       ^","       |","  App target (imports all modules, wires containers)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":null},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Key rules:"}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Protocol modules define abstractions only — no Forge dependency needed","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Feature modules import protocol modules and Forge"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"ViewModels and services never "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"import"},{"type":"text","text":" a concrete service module directly"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The app target is the only place that imports both protocol and concrete modules","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"anchor":"Best-Practices","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Best Practices"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Keep containers ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"module-scoped","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — if a container grows beyond its module’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"concerns, the module has too many responsibilities"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Make dependency properties ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"public"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — they are the module’s DI surface","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"protocol return types"}]},{"type":"text","text":" on all dependency properties"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Proxy cross-module dependencies rather than importing other feature modules"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://Forge/documentation/Forge":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A lightweight, compile-time safe dependency injection framework for Swift."}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/forge","identifier":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge","title":"Forge","role":"collection"},"doc://Forge/documentation/Forge/XcodePreviewSupport":{"title":"Xcode Preview Support","identifier":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/XcodePreviewSupport","url":"\/documentation\/forge\/xcodepreviewsupport","type":"topic","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Provide preview-safe mock factories that activate automatically in Xcode Previews.","type":"text"}],"role":"article"},"doc://Forge/documentation/Forge/Container":{"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/Container","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The base class for all dependency containers in Forge."}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Container"}],"url":"\/documentation\/forge\/container","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Container"}],"title":"Container"},"doc://Forge/documentation/Forge/SOLIDPrinciples":{"title":"SOLID Principles with Forge","identifier":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/SOLIDPrinciples","url":"\/documentation\/forge\/solidprinciples","type":"topic","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"How each SOLID principle maps to Forge usage, with practical Swift examples.","type":"text"}],"role":"article"}}}